<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/37766563-aastha-mehta"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1595003258i/37766563._UX100_CR0,3,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/37766563-aastha-mehta">Aastha Mehta</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">It is tough to read. It is not particularly fascinating to a layman who doesnt come from the field of linguistics. But you need to keep patience and g<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">It is tough to read. It is not particularly fascinating to a layman who doesnt come from the field of linguistics. But you need to keep patience and go through it by reading some outside material from the internet too. <br />Thats what I did. <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
